FBIS4-18653 "drweu068__a94029" FBIS-WEU-94-068-A Daily Report 8 April 1994 ANNEX Switzerland Former Iranian Prime Minister's Cousin Granted Asylum Former Iranian Prime Minister's Cousin Granted Asylum BR0704152594 Bern ATSA/SDAA Database in French 1235 GMT 7 Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY BR0704152594 Bern ATSA/SDAA Database French BFN [Unattributed report: "Fereydun Bakhtiari Authorized To Enter Switzerland"] [Text] Bern, 7 Apr (ATS) -- Fereydun Ilkhan Bakhtiar [name as received] has been granted approval to enter Switzerland. He thus will be able to register as an asylum seeker, Federal Refugee Office (ODR) spokesman Heinz Schoeni said Thursday [7 April]. A cousin of the former shah's prime minister, Shapur Bakhtiar, arrived at Geneva Airport without a passport on 22 March. Claiming to be in danger if he was sent back to Tehran, he spent the intervening period in Cointrin's [Geneva airport] transit area, under threat of expulsion back to Iran.
